projected bands structure

1. run pw.x with calculation = 'scf'
2. run pw.x with calculation = 'bands'
3. run projwfc.x with:
	&projwfc
	    outdir       = 'path/name/'
	    prefix       = 'name'
	    ngauss       = 0
	    degauss      = 0.01
	    DeltaE       = 0.005
	    kresolveddos = .true.
	    filpdos      = 'name.k'
	/
4. run script projwfc_to_bands.awk (ref: https://gitlab.com/QEF/q-e/-/tree/develop/PP/examples/projected_bands_example) 
  with command: awk -v firststate=XXX -v laststate=XXX -v ef=XXX -f path-to/projwfc_to_bands.awk projwfc.out > fileout
	Where first/laststate is specific orbital that you need (can be set exceed the actual state in case need to extract all). 
	ef is Fermi energy. path-to is path to awk script. 
	projwfc.out is your output of projwfc.x
 	fileout is ouput for plotting projected-bands.
5. plot your awk output (scatter plot with hilighted specific orbital)
	example:	for inbnd in range(nbnd):
			    plt.plot(data[:, inbnd, 1], data[:, inbnd, 2], c='black')
			    plt.scatter(data[:, inbnd, 1],
			                data[:, inbnd, 2],
			                c=data[:,inbnd, col],
		        	        s=10*data[:,inbnd, col],
		                	vmin=0, vmax=0.5)


